                                                                                                                       7                                      Injured Dias out for   three weeks
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                            
	New Delhi: Indian football team suffered a setback on Thursday when key midfielder Steven Dias was ruled out of action for three weeks because of a rib fracture.         
	Dias, who played a crucial role in Indias triumphs in two Nehru Cups and the AFC Challenge Cup, was accidentally hit on the chest by a rival player in the 1-2 defeat against Thailand at the Ambedkar Stadium on Wednesday.         
	He was taken out of the ground on a stretcher but he returned to play for a few minutes before being replaced by Clifford Miranda.         
	On Thursday, Dias complained of chest pain and was taken to a local hospital for X-ray.         
	Its a minor fracture but he wont be able to play for at least three weeks, said an official of the Indian team.                                                                                                                     
